Fix incorrect process exit value from "xml fo" (format).

xmlOutputBufferClose() returns the number of bytes written (or -1 on
error), not a success/failure boolean. foProcess() passed that byte
count through as the program exit status, so "xml fo" exited with
(bytes_written % 256) instead of 0 on success (most visible with
--omit-decl, where no XML declaration offsets the count).

See https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1231165

--- a/src/xml_format.c
+++ b/src/xml_format.c
@@ -339,7 +339,7 @@
                 child = child->next;
             }
         }
-        ret = xmlOutputBufferClose(buf);
+        ret = xmlOutputBufferClose(buf) >= 0 ? 0 : 1;
     }
     
     xmlFreeDoc(doc);
